{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nPackage the auto-lander loop service and wire it into the existing compose stack on the Gerrit box, single-instance. Split out of S5 (`perpetual-ultrasonic-raccoon`) to keep each unit loadable whole.\n\n## Files\n- `infra/compose/Dockerfile.autolander` — NEW: service image (installs the stdlib loop; `HEALTHCHECK` added by S5d).\n- `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml` — EDIT: add the `autolander` service (labeled `autoheal=true`, per S5d) + the `willfarrell/autoheal` sidecar (Docker socket `:ro`) + declare the autolander named state volume `external: true`.\n- `infra/scripts/compose-up.sh` — EDIT: add the autolander state volume to `SITE_SUBDIRS` (the incident-2731 drift gate: `config-check.sh` check 5 hard-fails CI when an `external: true` volume is missing from `SITE_SUBDIRS`).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `infra/compose/Dockerfile.autolander` (new) + the `autolander` compose service added to the existing `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml`.\n- [ ] **Single-instance guard:** the container acquires a POSIX advisory **file lock** (`flock` on a lockfile in its state volume) on start; a second copy fails to acquire it and exits. This `flock` is the **sole** single-instance mechanism — do NOT rely on `deploy.replicas: 1` (a Swarm-only key silently ignored by plain `docker compose`).\n- [ ] **State volume:** the autolander's named volume is declared `external: true` (the only volume pattern in this stack) and added to `SITE_SUBDIRS` in `compose-up.sh`; it holds the flock lockfile, the heartbeat file (S5d), the emergency-stop sentinel (S5d), and the drain recovery record (S5d), so all survive container recreation.\n- [ ] **Autoheal sidecar wired:** the `willfarrell/autoheal` service is present in `docker-compose.yml` with the Docker socket mounted **read-only**, and the `autolander` service carries the `autoheal=true` label so the sidecar manages it (the restart behaviour itself is exercised by S5d's hang test).\n- [ ] **Tests:** `docker compose config` validates (autolander + autoheal services, external volume, `autoheal=true` label present); a second container instance exits on the flock; `config-check.sh` check 5 passes (volume present in `SITE_SUBDIRS`)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783832719078880001,"uuid":"eafb80a5-4d2b-4d07-b755-a28505fb8059"}